I take on a small number of advisory relationships, usually seed to Series B, usually in education or AI. Two things tend to be useful. One is the founder stuff: leading a team you didn't expect to be leading, making calls with half the information, the particular weirdness of managing people more experienced than you. The other is product, hands-on: send me the prototype and I'll walk it with you, from what to build next to how the team should be built to build it. Sometimes that's a standing engagement, sometimes it's a call a month. I invest early too. If any of that sounds useful, [write to me](mailto:hi@prannoy.com).
